Icelyn Brathius has 17 years old and is part of a group of people who live at the top of a mountain above the clouds and away from the nameless threat down below that threatens their very survival.

Three hundred years ago, something terrifying arose and pushed humanity to the brink of extinction. Now, a small remnant ‚Äì the descendants of the few survivors who were able to escape the massacre below ‚Äì lives above the clouds, on the top of a Mountain.

And when everything you thought you knew turns out to be wrong? What would you do?

The Threat Below is a fantasy dystopian by J.S.Latshaw, the book writing is simple which makes reading easy. It is the first time that I read this kind of book and I was pleasantly surprised. I really enjoy this book.

Thank you very much Jason Latshaw for the book.

